personalStatement:
Leonhard Euler , born onApril 15, 1707in Basel ( Switzerland ) and died at the age of 76 on September 7, 1783 (September 18 , 1783 in the Gregorian calendar ) in Saint Petersburg ( Russian Empire ), is a Swiss mathematician and physicist , who spent most of his life in the Russian Empire and Germany . He was notably a member of the Royal Prussian Academy of Sciences in Berlin .

Euler made important discoveries in fields as varied as calculus and graph theory . He also introduced much of the terminology and notation of modern mathematics , especially for mathematical analysis , such as the notion of mathematical function . He is also known for his work in mechanics , fluid dynamics , optics and astronomy or triangle geometry.
